    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Exodus 38</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Ex038-P151v-L11_trl" n="11" prev="ADub.III.73.002.037.trl.xml#Ex037-P151v-L11_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And he made the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            altar of burnt offering of acacia wood, five cubits the length
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            of it, and five cubits the breadth of it, foursquare, and three cubits
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            the height of it.</l>
                        <l n="2">And he made its horns
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            on the four corners of it. Its horns were of one piece with it,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            and he overlaid it with bronze.</l>
                        <l n="3">And he made
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            all the equipment of the altar: the cauldrons, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            brushes, and the cups, and the forks,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            and the censers. He made all of its equipment
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            of bronze.</l>
                        <l n="4">And he made a grate for the altar, network
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            of bronze, under its ledge<ref target="#fn1" type="noteAnchor" />,
                            below, halfway up.</l>
                        <l n="5">
                            <milestone unit="page" n="152r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            And he <supplied reason="lost">cast</supplied> four rings for the four
                            ends of the bronze grate:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            places for the poles.</l>
                        <l n="6">And he made the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            poles of acacia wood, and overlaid them with bronze.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="7">And he put the poles to the rings
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            on the sides of the altar, to carry it with them.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            He made it of hollow boards.</l>
                        <l n="8">And he made the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            basin of bronze, and the place of it of bronze,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            with the mirrors of the women who gathered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            at the door of the tent of meeting.</l>
                        <l n="9">And he made the court:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            on the south side, southward, the court’s curtains
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            of twined linen, a hundred cubits,</l>
                        <l n="10">Their pillars
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            twenty, and their bronze bases twenty, the hooks of the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            pillars and their bands of silver.</l>
                        <l n="11">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            And for the north side: the curtains were a hundred cubits, their
                            pillars were twenty,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            and their bases of bronze twenty, the hooks of the pillars
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            and their bands of silver.</l>
                        <l n="12">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            for the west side: curtains of fifty cubits, their pillars ten,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            and their bases ten, the hooks of the pillars and their bands
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            of silver.</l>
                        <l n="13">And for the east side,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            eastward: fifty cubits.</l>
                        <l n="14">Curtains of fifteen cubits
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            to the one side, their pillars three, and their bases three.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="152v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="15">And for the second side, on this side and on this side of the
                            court gate,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            curtains of fifteen cubits, their pillars three, and their bases
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            three.</l>
                        <l n="16">All the <supplied reason="lost">curtains</supplied> of the court
                            all around were of twined linen.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="17">And the bases for the pillars were of bronze, the hooks of the pillars
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            and their bands of silver, and the overlaying of their capitals also
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            of silver, and all the pillars of the court were banded with silver.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                        <l n="18">And the cover for the gate of the court was the work of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            embroiderer, of blue and purple and scarlet silk, and twined
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            linen, and twenty cubits in the length, and five cubits the height in
                            its breadth,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            opposite to the curtains of the court.</l>
                        <l n="19">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            And their pillars were four, and their bases of bronze four,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            their hooks of silver, and the overlaying of their capitals and their
                            bands of silver.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                        <l n="20">And all the pegs of the tabernacle and of the court all around
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            of bronze.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            <emph>Parashat Pekudei</emph></l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="21">This is the supervision
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            of the tabernacle, of the tabernacle of law, as it was destined,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            according to the word of Moses, the work of the Levites by the hand
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            of Ithamar, son <addSpan spanTo="#add001" /><emph>of Aaron</emph><anchor
                                xml:id="add001" />, the priest.</l>
                        <l n="22">And Bezalel, son
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            of Uri, son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah, made all
                            <milestone unit="page" n="153r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            that the Lord commanded Moses.</l>
                        <l n="23">And with him was Oholiab,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan, a master |workman|, and an embroiderer,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            and a needleworker in blue and in purple and in scarlet silk,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            and linen.</l>
                        <l n="24">All the gold that was used for the work,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            in all the work of the Holy: and the gold of the wave offering
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            was twenty-nine kantar, and seven <supplied reason="lost"
                                >hundred</supplied> and thirty mithqals, by the mithqal
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            of the Holy.</l>
                        <l n="25">And the ransom silver taken
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            from them that were counted of the congregation was a hundred kantars,
                            and a thousand and seven hundred
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            and seventy-five mithqals, by the mithqal of the Holy.</l>
                        <l n="26">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            A <emph>gög</emph><ref target="#fn2" type="noteAnchor" /> per head, that
                            is, half a mithqal, by the mithqal of the Holy,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            for every one that went to be counted, from twenty years old
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            and upward, for six hundred thousand and three thousand and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            five hundred and fifty.</l>
                        <l n="27">And the hundred kantars of silver
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            were for casting the bases of the Holy and the bases of the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            veil, a hundred bases of the hundred kantars, a kantar for a base.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="28">And of the thousand and seven hundred and seventy-
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            <supplied reason="lost">five</supplied> he made hooks for the pillars,
                            and overlaid their capitals, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            banded them.</l>
                        <l n="29">And the bronze of the wave offering was
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            seventy kantars and two thousand and four hundred mithqals.</l>
                        <l n="30">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            And with it he made the bases of the door of the tent of meeting, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            the bronze altar, and the bronze grate which was for it,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="153v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            and all the equipment of the altar,</l>
                        <l n="31">And the bases
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            of the court all around, and the bases of the court gate,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            and all the pegs of the tabernacle, and all the pegs
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Ex038-P153v-L4_trl" n="4" next="ADub.III.73.002.039.trl.xml#Ex039-P153v-L4_trl" />
                            of the court all around.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
